BPA lowers Tuesday peak , firm power $ 0 . 50 / MWh . Bonneville Power Administration ( BPA ) lowered firm peak power prices for Tuesday by 50 cents per megawatt hour ( MWh ) , the agency said Monday . BPA still offered 300 megawatts of firm peak power , but lowered prices to $ 15 . 00 per megawatt hour ( MWh ) for Northwest sales and $ 16 . 00 for California - Oregon border ( COB ) sales . Prices for non - firm power during shoulder hours on Monday ( 0600 , 1100 - 1700 and 2100 - 2200 PST ) were unchanged at $ 11 . 00 for Northwest and $ 12 . 00 for COB . Prices for firm and non - firm power during off - peak hours on Monday were unchanged at $ 9 . 00 per MWh for all deliveries . ( ( - - Los Angeles bureau + 1 213 655 6761 ) ) 
